Background

		Mr. Alexander J. Matturri, Jr., also known as Alex, CFA, J.D., has been the Chief Executive Officer of S&P Dow Jones Indices LLC since July 2, 2012. Mr. Matturri served as an Executive Managing Director of S&P Indices. He served as Director of Global Index Management of Northern Trust Corporation. He served as Senior Vice President and Director of Global Equity Index Management of Northern Trust Global Investments. He joined Northern Trust Global Investments in 2003. ... At Deutsche, he served as director and senior index investment strategist. From 1987 until joining Deutsche in 2000, he served as vice president and division head at The Bank of New York where he managed the Special Investment Products group which provided investment management, product development and trading for equity derivatives and quantitative strategies. He was a pioneer in the use of equity derivatives and exchange traded funds in institutional and high-net-worth portfolios. In 1993, he started The Bank of New York’s transition management business which was one of the first providers of portfolio transition and asset reallocation services. His experience before The Bank of New York included roles as a risk arbitrage analyst at Donaldson, Lufkin & Jenrette and security analyst at First Fidelity Bank. He has been a Director of S&P Dow Jones Indices LLC since July 2, 2012. He is a Chartered Financial Analyst and is admitted as an attorney in New York and New Jersey. He is also a member of the CFA Institute and The New York Society of Security Analysts. Mr. Matturri holds a BS in finance with honors from Lehigh University and a JD from Syracuse University College of Law.Read Full Background




